K with a certain institution over another depending on your comfort.%0a%3c %0a%3c From the wide use of this word as both a verb and an adjective, we can understand better the belief system of the Nacirema culture. The Nacirema seem to value the long-term preservation of materials, ranging from currency to memory and even bodily fluids such as blood and sperm. Their culture revolves around maintaining the past for unknown future purposes. Considering the many monetary concepts the word refers to, the Nacirema appear to be a capitalistic society, placing a lot of value on money. The use of the word “bank” also suggests the Nacirema often took part in gambling and other sorts of risk-taking, which can be illustrated in the phrase “banking on who will win.” The fact that the same word is strangely used to mean a financial institution, part of a river, and a collection of snow may imply that the Nacirema saw great value in nature just as they do the institution that they trust to safeguard their currency. %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
